9 Relating to Mobile County; to further provide for the
10 appointment of temporary judges of probate.
11 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
12 Section 1. Section 45-49-85.42, Code of Alabama 1975,
13 is amended to read as follows:
14 "§45-49-85.42
15 (a)(1) If the regularly elected Judge of Probate of
16 Mobile County is incompetent from any legal cause,
17 incapacitated, absent or will be absent from sickness, or
18 otherwise disqualified from acting as judge, the judge of
19 probate or the chief clerk shall certify the fact of
20 incompetency, incapacity, absence, sickness, or
21 disqualification to the presiding judge of the circuit court
22 of the county, and the presiding judge of the circuit court,
23 upon that certificate, shall appoint a person an individual
24 learned in the law, practicing and residing in the county, to
25 act as temporary judge of probate. At any time when the
26 regularly elected judge of probate of the county files a
27 certificate in the office of the circuit clerk of the county
28 that he or she is no longer incompetent, from any legal cause,
