57 jurisdiction and authority and discharge the duties of the
58 judge of probate, and the judgments, orders, and decrees made
59 or rendered by any of them shall be entered on the records of
60 the probate court, and shall have the force and effect, and
61 shall be subject to revision or appeal or by other revisory
62 remedy, of judgments, orders, and decrees of the probate court
63 or of the judge of probate. Neither the regularly elected
64 judge of probate of the county, nor the surety on his or her
65 bond, shall be responsible for any of the acts or decisions
66 made by any temporary judge of probate, failure to act or
67 report by any temporary judge of probate, or any of the acts
